        <MudText>
            Making is a <b>"labor of love"</b>. The dough is kneaded until it's soft and smooth, then filled with a sweet mixture of cooked chana dal and jaggery. The filled dough is then rolled out and cooked until golden brown. The result is a deliciously sweet and satisfying treat that's a beloved part of our culinary heritage.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5">Remembering Holige Gowramma</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">A Legacy of Culinary Excellence</MudText>
        <MudText>
            She was a renowned figure in the culinary world of Karnataka, known for her exceptional skills in making Holige. Despite the challenges she faced, Gowramma's dedication to her craft led her to become internationally famous. Her story is a testament to the power of perseverance , passion & Strength of Women Power.
        </MudText>

        <!-- More details about Holige Gowramma -->
        <MudText>
            Gowramma's journey began in a small village in Sringeri, where she learned cooking from her mother. She was well-versed in making all kinds of south Indian dishes, especially sweets. Her dedication & perfection helped her family & sorroundings.
            Her Holige was praised by many, and she received numerous orders. This prompted her to start a business from home, which continues to operate out of the same outlet.
        </MudText>

